article.description: Ryan Bowie made his final home game memorable, hitting six 3-pointers and scoring 24 points to help spark Texas-San Antonio to a 74-53 rout of Southern Mississippi Saturday afternoon.
article.headline: Bowie leads Texas-San Antonio rout over Southern Miss, 74-53
article.linkText: Bowie leads Texas-San Antonio rout over Southern Miss, 74-53
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Ryan Bowie made his final home game memorable, hitting six 3-pointers and scoring 24 points to help spark Texas-San Antonio to a 74-53 rout of Southern Mississippi Saturday afternoon. The senior scored 20 points or more for the 15th time this season, including each of his last five games. Bowie hit four 3-pointers in the first half, sparking the Roadrunners to an 11-point advantage by halftime and the team outscored the Golden Eagles by 10 points in the second half. Texas-San Antonio (5-23, 3-12 Conference USA) shot 25 of 49 from the field (51.0 percent) and 14 of 22 from beyond the arc (63.6 percent). Bowie was 6 of 14 from the field, including 6 of 11 for deep. Christian Wilson added 16 points and Phillip Jones pulled down 11 rebounds. Kourtlin Jackson scored 11 points for Southern Miss (7-18, 4-10).
